			<div></div><br><blockquote><hr>josahd wrote:<br><i>"</i><span><i> In other words, I'm not at all opposed to a &quot;loss&quot; in DPS/Aggro, but that loss cannot be to such an extent that it encourages us not to use a shield, such as it is today.&quot;</i><br><br>Frodlin,<br><br>The aggro and dps loss SHOULD discourage you from using a shield in all circumstances, just like a knight isn't going to use a 1h/shield in all circumstances, and in fact most maintain a dps and tanking weapon set.<br></span><div></div><br><hr></blockquote><p><br>Of course, I would only want to use 1h/shield when tanking challenging content, like you.</p><p>I should lose a very small amount of aggro... like you, and I should lose some DPS, like you. When I'm not tanking challenging content, I should use 2h or dual wield, or when tanking less than challenging content, I should use DW or 2h.</p><p>It should not discourage me from using 1h/shield WHILE TANKING though, just like you.</p><p>I am so dead serious about this issue... if we do not get what we deserve, I will simply petition for Above cap AC for shields and shield block to be removed from Everquest entirely, and all of our AA's refunded. The tanking world is that imbalanced at this time due to shield benefits which only benefit 2 tank classes.</p>
