			>
			<div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div>"but why is this an issue in a thread about downward scaling tools...."<br><br>With shields and Shield Block practical for Warriors and no greater loss of our secondary role (heavey DPS) than Knights experiance in their secondary roles (battleflield healer/rooter, puller/pet summoner, etc.) when they equip a shield...<br><br>I would equip a shield in lesser content and not use any defensive disciplines at all, use offensive disciplines insted, and let damage shields nibble away at mobs that hit me for very little when they can manage to hit me (free DPS) while beating them to death with my heavy DPS thanks to shield appropriate ratio weapon.<br><br>When I'm actually in maximum defensive mode, I'm using Defensive. Vs. the hardest mobs, I take a 30-40% loss of DPS by equipping a shield AND a futher loss of DPS on top of that because I'm in Defensive.<br><br>Even if Warrriors were tagged to use Eulogy, I would do more DPS with a 2Hander (better damage bonus). But in lesser group content, I can turtle with a shield and do heavy DPS because I need not do <u>anything </u>for good avoidance/miotigation.<br><br>So sword and board is a downward scaling tool (or will be when we get Shieldmate weapons) because it actually gets better in lesser content where I'm not cutting down my DPS by using Defensive.<br><br>It preserves the tanking gap and prevents Knights from finding ever more content trivial to them where they can equip a shield and tank like a Warrior AND then focus on utility. I too can equip a shield and focus on DPS (less than my maximum, but still quite heavy). Given a choice between a Knight with a shield and a Warriror with a shield, groups would not say - Well the Knight can tank just like the Warrior but they have all that utility. Rather they would say, <u>Knights have all that utility, but Warriors have more survivability and do good DPS.</u> That's why I rolled a Warrior and that's why y'all didn't.<br><br>Admittedly, I need faster refresh offensive disciplines to make this truely practical, but at this point any bone SoE tosses Warriors is better than nothing. And my intended greater weapon skills should accomplish most of what is needed anyway with shield appropriate weapons.<br><br><b>Knights are using shields to advertise in both high and lesser content - we tank just like Warriors AND we have all that utility. Unfortunately with shields and Shield Block the way they are - they're telling the truth.</b><br><div></div><p>Message Edited by Battleblade-Xegony on <span class=date_text>03-13-2006</span> <span class=time_text>04:19 AM</span>	
