		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<div></div><p>Warrior Sheilds still would not adres the disparity cause between Knight Shields and Warriors, since it would still continue to exist vs DWing Warriors.</p><p>This is what Battleblade and to a lesser extent Frodlin (who's views are actually pretty balanced) are missing in this respect.</p><p>The solution is not simply to inflate Shield use for Warriors, as this invariably leads to some, even if it's small, reduction of DPS and Aggro on their part while still not solving the issue of the disparity caused by Shields vs Warriors in all other set-ups. I strongly believe it is a two part solution.</p><p>First Warriors need a boost that effects their base abilities to counter shields. Shield block is not introduced until the mid 60s and is done in three segments as you level, so accordingly Warriors should getsome AC boost, Mitigation or avoidance boost that counters this, where they are effected by shield block. Such a boost would beindependent of the Warrior weapon set-ups, and so the amount should be balanced accordingly.</p><p>Second Shields should be made more viable as an option to Warriors, although they would still take a DPS and Aggro hit with Shields, this is more then made up for by the general boost they receive above.</p><p>This is based on the ideal that instead of Shields being a &quot;step closer&quot; for knights, it should instead be considered the knight standard with 2-Handers being a &quot;step back&quot; This is acheived by seperating the gap between Warrior and knight based on the shielded knight vs the unshielded Warrior.</p>	
		</td></tr>
