			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=15715'>







<img src="http://i12.photobucket.com/albums/a247/Ridefort/soecheerleader.jpg" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=15299#M15299">400</a> of 481
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 116 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<div></div><em>Frod,<br></em><blockquote><em>&quot;if it's not desirable to continue upgrades which trivialize everything&quot;<br></em></blockquote><em>I'm glad you're not saying that's the case, b/c it's certainly not currently the case that the sum total of knight abilities vs group content trivialize everything. And if content is not being trivialized, there's no reason to even mention the word nerf. Focus on getting your own issues taken care of, not on other classes. Threatening &quot;nerfs&quot; if you don't get your way isn't cool (which is effectively what you've done here). Also, it's flat out overestimating your influence- if you haven't managed to get warrior tanking issues fixed, what makes you think you have the influence to nerf knights? The end result is just a lot of bickering on forums with no impact on the game (I think the thing people are getting away from here is EQ design is not done by comittee on public forums, it's done by professional game designers. And while they may sometimes incorporate suggestions from the playerbase, ultimately, the players- even class correspondents- don't make game design decisions).</em><br><p>I agree with you Josahd... but I can certainly say &quot;In my opinion, a nerf needs to happen&quot;, even though I don't necessarily think it does, although it's REAL close in my opinion to needing to eliminate shield block and above cap AC for everyone and simply returning the AA.</p><p>My opinion though... is nothing but that, my opinion. I have zero delusions about it meaning anything else. I'm certainly in a position to be able to say &quot;this is my opinion, that things have spiralled out of control, and need to either be reigned in, or the others boosted&quot;, but that doesn't mean that we as players cannot postulate on what we think is proper.</p><blockquote><p><i></i></p><p><em>&quot;When grouped with a warrior, if EQ is to be truly balanced... you, having more roles than the warrior should not be tanking, and the warrior should be. &quot;<br></em></p></blockquote><p><em>When I'm grouped with a warrior from my guild... the warrior generally does tank. So I guess EQ isn't all that unbalanced after all. For EQ to be &quot;truly balanced&quot;, all classes should be of roughly equal desirability in groups and in raids. For the game to be &quot;truly balanced&quot;, the gap between a knight and a warrior in groups should <u><b>never</b></u> favor warrior tanks to the exclusion of knights. I.E., The situation should never be &quot;We need a tank.... grab a warrior! Oh... wait, haven't seen a warrior lfg for the last 15 minutes, I guess we can take that SK over there lfg....&quot;. The situation should never be, when an SK is in a group, &quot;Ok, we're all set.... just need a tank!&quot; (to head into challenging content). Both of those scenarios have played out more than once in EQ's history.<br><br>My point is- any adjustments to warrior tanking power must be measured carefully to prevent history from repeating itself, and prevent the gap from becoming excessive.<br></em></p><p>I pretty much agree with this wholeheartedly. I don't like the constant see saw of imbalance, and believe it or not, I hate being too powerful in relation to knights as much as I hate being too weak. I have a ton of friends that play knights, and it irritates me if they're not having fun because they're not strong enough. Now is not that time though, at this point, warriors are in deep trouble.</p>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<img src="http://i12.photobucket.com/albums/a247/Ridefort/frodsig.gif" height=110 width=300><br><br>Warrior Class Correspondent<br>"54 random people is no more a raid than a heap of building materials is a house"
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
